Workshop on Materialized Views : Techniques and Applications ( In Co-operation with [ 1 ] ACM Sigmod ) Friday , June 7 , 1996 Le Centre Sheraton Hotel , [ 2 ] Montreal , Canada . CALL FOR PAPERS and ATTENDANCE _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
[ 3 ] Materialized views have recently seen a renewed interest in the research and commercial communitites because of their applications in warehousing , schema integration in heterogeneous databases , visualization , integrity constraints , query optimization , and decision support . Leading database vendors are currently implementing or planning to implement materialized views in some form . Several database research groups in academia are also studying materialized views .
The aim of the workshop is to bring together people working on various aspects of materialized views - their storage , maintenance , implementation , and applications . What are the problems that need to be solved to efficiently implement materialized views ? What are the various consistency options and performance tradeoffs in maintaining materialized views ? What are the new applications for materialized views ?
The setting will be informal , and will encourage discussion and interaction . We especially encourage the submission of short papers dealing with specific problems , things that did n't work , desirable features , and position papers . An informal proceedings will be published . There will be a $ 50 registration fee .
PAPER SUBMISSIONS :
We invite papers for presentation and discussion at the workshop . Send a postscript copy of the paper by email ( preferable ) , or five hard copies on paper to the address below . The page limit on all submissions is 10 pages , double spaced , 10 pt minimum .
